    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="603"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/1021: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 12, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Department’s 54, September 3, 5 p.m. Commercial Attaché’s Special Weekly
                    Financial Report, November 25, 1935.<note n="35" xml:id="d603fn35">Not found in
                        Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The decision of the Spanish Foreign Exchange Control Board that certificates to
                    importers stating the exact amount of foreign currency which they will receive
                    in settlement of peseta deposits covering applications for exchange to pay for
                    imports will be issued only in the case of imports from England, France, Holland
                    and Switzerland, is regarded as an extension of the discrimination against which
                    you were directed to protest in the Department’s telegram above cited. You are
                    requested, in your discretion, therefore, to take this matter up again with the
                    appropriate authorities at the earliest opportunity, and urge-strongly that the
                    same treatment be accorded to imports from the United States as to those from
                    any other country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
